 📊 Retail Sales Forecasting & Strategic Optimization

 🚀 Overview
This project focuses on building an advanced retail sales forecasting system combined with strategic revenue optimization insights. It leverages time-series modeling and business analytics to improve forecasting accuracy and support data-driven financial decision-making.

The project demonstrates how forecasting models can be integrated with business strategy to enhance financial planning, reporting, and market expansion initiatives.


 🎯 Objectives
•	Improve sales forecasting accuracy using advanced time-series models  
•	Analyze historical sales data across regions, categories, and segments  
•	Generate actionable insights for:
o	Revenue optimization  
o	Product mix strategy  
o	Market expansion  
o	Support business and financial decision-making through predictive analytics  

 📂 Dataset
•	Source: Public Superstore retail dataset  
o	Key Features:
o	Order Date, Sales, Profit, Quantity  
o	Region, Category, Sub-category  
o	Customer Segment, Discount  

 
 
🛠️ Methodology

 1. Data Preprocessing
•	Converted date columns into time-series format  
•	Extracted Year, Month, Quarter features  
•	Aggregated data at daily and monthly levels  

 2. Baseline Model
•	Simple Moving Average (7-day)
•	Used as a benchmark for performance comparison  

 3. Advanced Forecasting Model
•	Holt-Winters Triple Exponential Smoothing
•	Captures trend, seasonality, and level components  
•	Applied on monthly aggregated sales data  

 4. Model Evaluation
•	Metric Used: Mean Absolute Error (MAE)  
•	Achieved: ~25% improvement in forecasting accuracy compared to baseline  

 5. Forecasting Output
•	Generated 6-month forward sales forecast  
•	Supports:
•	Budgeting  
•	Inventory planning  
•	Revenue projections  

 
